---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Terms and disclaimer: how to use True Trip Costs, and what it is not"
  description="A plain-language note on using True Trip Costs: we publish checked, dated money information, not professional advice. Rules and fees change, so verify anything critical with the official source before you travel."
>
  <Nav />
  <main class="wrap">

    <section class="pv-hero">
      <p class="lab">Terms and disclaimer</p>
      <h1>What this site is, and what it is not.</h1>
      <p class="pv-lede">The short version: we publish money information for travelers, checked against official sources and dated on the page. It is not legal, financial, immigration, tax or veterinary advice, and rules change. Before you book, pay or fly, confirm anything critical with the official source we link to.</p>
      <p class="pv-date">Last updated: 23 July 2026</p>
    </section>

    <section class="pv-prose">
      <h2>Information, not advice</h2>
      <p>Everything here is general information for travelers leaving the US. It is not legal advice, financial or investment advice, immigration or visa advice, tax advice, insurance advice, or veterinary advice, and using this site does not create a professional relationship of any kind. Your situation has details we cannot know: your passport, your bank, your card, your pet, your dates, your circumstances. Where the stakes are high, a qualified professional or the official body is the right source, not a website.</p>

      <h2>We check and date, and rules still change</h2>
      <p>Every guide shows the month it was last checked, and the fees most likely to move carry their own checked date beside the number. We check figures against primary sources: the government department, tax authority, central bank or official operator that actually sets the fee. Our <a href="/methodology">methodology page</a> explains how that works.</p>
      <p>Even so, rules move without notice, exchange rates drift daily, and a figure that was right when we checked it can be wrong by the time you read it. We do not promise that everything here is current, complete or free of error. Treat our numbers as a well-researched starting point, and confirm anything that would cost you money or stop you boarding with the official source. We link those sources on every guide for exactly this reason.</p>

      <h2>The calculator is an estimate, not a quote</h2>
      <p>The cost calculator on each guide, and the comparison pages, produce our own estimates built from stated assumptions. They are there to help you plan and compare, not to quote a price. Your real trip will differ. Every assumption is spelled out under the total so you can see what the number is made of and change it.</p>

      <h2>If you spot something wrong</h2>
      <p>Tell us. When we get a detail wrong we correct it against the primary source, note what changed in that guide, and update the checked date. Write to <a href="mailto:privacy@truetripcosts.com">privacy@truetripcosts.com</a>. We would rather hear about a mistake and fix it than leave it standing.</p>

      <h2>Affiliate links and the products we point to</h2>
      <p>Some links on this site earn us a commission if you buy through them. Those are labeled "we may earn a commission" every time, and the ones that earn us nothing are labeled too, so you always know which is which. The price is the same to you either way. We only suggest something when it genuinely saves money or trouble, and when the honest answer is that you do not need anything, we say so.</p>
      <p>We are not the seller. Products and services are provided by the companies behind them, on their terms, and any purchase is a contract between you and them. We do not control their pricing, their coverage, their small print or their service, and we are not responsible for it. Read the policy or the quote before you buy, especially for insurance, where what is covered and what is excluded is the whole point.</p>

      <h2>Links to other sites</h2>
      <p>We link to government pages, official operators and other outside sites. We do not control them and we are not responsible for their content, their accuracy or what they do with your data. A link is not an endorsement of everything on the other end of it.</p>

      <h2>Limits on our liability</h2>
      <p>This site is provided as it is, without warranties of any kind, express or implied, including any implied warranty of accuracy, fitness for a particular purpose, or uninterrupted availability. To the fullest extent the law allows, True Trip Costs is not liable for any loss or damage arising from your use of this site or from anything you did or did not do because of it, including missed flights, refused entry, unexpected fees, currency losses, insurance claims, or costs connected with moving a pet. You are responsible for your own travel decisions.</p>
      <p>Nothing here limits any liability that cannot lawfully be limited.</p>

      <h2>Using the site</h2>
      <p>You are welcome to read, quote and link to these guides. Please do not scrape or republish them wholesale, present our figures as your own, or use the site in a way that damages it or interferes with anyone else using it. The words, guides, charts and images on this site are ours unless credited otherwise.</p>

      <h2>Who this is for</h2>
      <p>These guides are written for travelers leaving the US. The site is run from the United States, and it is aimed at adults planning their own travel. It is not directed at children.</p>

      <h2>Changes to these terms</h2>
      <p>If this page changes, we will update the date at the top. For anything you are unsure about, write to <a href="mailto:privacy@truetripcosts.com">privacy@truetripcosts.com</a>. Our <a href="/privacy">privacy note</a> covers what we collect and what we do with it.</p>
    </section>

  </main>
  <Footer />

  <style>
    .pv-hero{padding:48px 0 6px;max-width:680px}
    .pv-hero h1{margin:6px 0 14px}
    .pv-lede{font-size:17px;line-height:1.55;color:var(--ink);margin:0}
    .pv-date{font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);margin:16px 0 0}
    .pv-prose{padding:34px 0 64px;max-width:680px}
    .pv-prose h2{margin:26px 0 8px;font-size:19px}
    .pv-prose h2:first-child{margin-top:0}
    .pv-prose p{font-size:16px;line-height:1.65;color:var(--ink);margin:0 0 14px}
    .pv-prose a{color:var(--teal-deep);font-weight:500;text-decoration:underline;text-underline-offset:2px}
  </style>
</Base>
